00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:35,410
The Chinese Communist Party seeks to create
a harmonious society.

9
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:42,780
And for them, “harmonious” means highly
regulated, tightly controlled, and most importantly,

10
00:00:42,780 --> 00:00:45,620
looking perfect on the surface.

11
00:00:45,620 --> 00:00:51,100
Which is why when Party officials see this,
it’s just not ok.

12
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:52,329
Chaotic intersections?

13
00:00:52,329 --> 00:00:54,940
We can’t have that.

14
00:00:54,940 --> 00:00:58,290
So should we install functioning traffic lights?

15
00:00:58,290 --> 00:01:00,970
Assign police to direct traffic?

16
00:01:00,970 --> 00:01:02,080
No!

17
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:06,990
The problem is all those poor people riding
scooters and motorbikes.

18
00:01:06,990 --> 00:01:09,450
We can’t have this.

19
00:01:09,450 --> 00:01:10,829
Or this.

20
00:01:10,829 --> 00:01:12,149
Arrest them!

21
00:01:12,149 --> 00:01:14,409
Haha, no seriously.

22
00:01:14,409 --> 00:01:15,909
Arrest them.

23
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:20,869
Recently, officials in Dongguan city—which
is here, in Guangdong province—have tried

24
00:01:20,869 --> 00:01:23,350
to harmonize the city streets...

25
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:27,850
...with a large-scale seizure of scooters
and motorcycles.\h

26
00:01:27,850 --> 00:01:33,759
Yes, the Public Security Bureau ordered its
police to break into people’s homes and

27
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:35,679
snag their vehicles.\h

28
00:01:35,679 --> 00:01:40,220
“Many motorcycles driving on the streets
or parked in front of residents’ homes were

29
00:01:40,220 --> 00:01:42,779
seized by the police.

30
00:01:42,779 --> 00:01:47,240
Delivery men came out of the door to find
out their vehicles have been towed away by

31
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,100
the police.”

32
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:54,920
In the past couple weeks, a surge of videos
showing Chinese police taking parked motorcycles

33
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:58,740
off the street began circulating on the internet.

34
00:01:58,740 --> 00:02:03,329
They would even take the motorcycles right
off people’s property, without giving any

35
00:02:03,329 --> 00:02:05,659
notice.

36
00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:08,780
What if you’re already on your motorcycle?

37
00:02:08,780 --> 00:02:10,349
Don’t worry!

38
00:02:10,349 --> 00:02:13,530
Police can solve that problem for you.

39
00:02:13,530 --> 00:02:18,190
I wonder why this guy is speeding away from
the police.

40
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:23,269
He should really just pull over, and let the
police take his bike away.

41
00:02:23,269 --> 00:02:27,000
What if you refuse to get off your scooter?

42
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,159
Police can solve that problem, too.

43
00:02:29,159 --> 00:02:32,799
There’s lots of policemen and only one of
you.

44
00:02:32,799 --> 00:02:35,840
\h
And frankly, most people whose motorcycles

45
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:39,860
are being taken aren’t so lucky.

46
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:44,310
“You dare fight back?

47
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:45,310
You dare fight back?”

48
00:02:45,310 --> 00:02:46,590
Yeah, how dare he fight back!

49
00:02:46,590 --> 00:02:50,500
What, does he think he owns his own property?

50
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:53,350
This is communist China, comrade.

51
00:02:53,350 --> 00:02:55,469
“This is not your motorcycle.

52
00:02:55,469 --> 00:02:57,329
This is the Nation’s motorcycle!”

53
00:02:57,329 --> 00:02:59,920
Your motorcycle belongs to the people!

54
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:03,079
And by the people, we mean us, the police.

55
00:03:03,079 --> 00:03:07,099
Truly, this is for your own protection.

56
00:03:07,099 --> 00:03:11,129
And it’s important your children understand
this, too.

57
00:03:11,129 --> 00:03:15,079
Maybe you can just push your kids in a wheelbarrow
instead.

58
00:03:15,079 --> 00:03:21,269
Unsurprisingly, this mass and arbitrary seizure
of motorcycles left some people feeling hopeless.

59
00:03:21,269 --> 00:03:22,269
“Tragic.

60
00:03:22,269 --> 00:03:23,980
Went to buy some stuff, and I lost a bike.”

61
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:25,879
And it’s left others furious.

62
00:03:25,879 --> 00:03:26,879
“How come you law enforcement can have motorcycles?

63
00:03:26,879 --> 00:03:27,879
Why don’t you walk?”

64
00:03:27,879 --> 00:03:28,879
“Our motorcycles are stolen right from our
homes.

65
00:03:28,879 --> 00:03:32,530
Tell me how can I live like this?

66
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:38,292
Tell me the reason for this.

67
00:03:38,292 --> 00:03:39,292
I’m scared to go out because my motorcycle
will be taken.”

68
00:03:39,292 --> 00:03:43,230
For a lot of people in China, their motorcycle
or scooter is their livelihood.

69
00:03:43,230 --> 00:03:48,120
Like if you’re a delivery worker, and police
decide they want to take your scooter...and

70
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:50,379
also your cargo.

71
00:03:50,379 --> 00:03:55,819
This delivery boy is threatening to commit
suicide because police are taking his scooter—and

72
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:59,980
without it he loses his way to make a living.

73
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:05,659
So what’s really driving Chinese authorities’
push to seize people’s scooters and motorcycles?

74
00:04:05,659 --> 00:04:08,580
I’ll get to that after the break.

75
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:10,060
Welcome back.

76
00:04:10,060 --> 00:04:14,909
At the end of March, the city of Dongguan
organized a police gathering, instructing

77
00:04:14,909 --> 00:04:19,410
them to confiscate “illegal” scooters
and motorcycles from civilians.

78
00:04:19,410 --> 00:04:25,610
Now, it’s true that some of these vehicles
are unregistered or aren’t compliant.

79
00:04:25,610 --> 00:04:30,410
But if that were the real problem, there’d
be a much easier and less brutal way to solve

80
00:04:30,410 --> 00:04:31,410
it.\h

81
00:04:31,410 --> 00:04:36,200
Officially, this new policy—or you might
call it a “political campaign”—was triggered

82
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:41,780
