88
00:05:06,820 --> 00:05:12,160
And in several other big cities in China,
motorcycles and/or scooters are also banned

89
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:15,610
or regulated for reasons I mentioned earlier.

90
00:05:15,610 --> 00:05:19,220
Officials claim it’s in the interest of
public safety.

91
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:24,000
Because Chinese officials truly care about
the safety of the people.

92
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:29,200
Whether it’s pedestrians...

93
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:31,560
Street vendors...

94
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,950
and especially children.

95
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:39,740
They always think of the children.

96
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:45,750
But surprisingly, not everyone believes these
latest motorcycle seizures *are* really about

97
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:47,120
safety.

98
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:51,900
Some citizens suspect the policy is used to
“clean up” the streets by getting poor

99
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:54,740
people out of the public view.

100
00:05:54,740 --> 00:06:00,730
When police confiscate the scooters and motorcycles,
they often say they don’t meet regulations,

101
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:01,800
or they’re unlicensed.

102
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:07,180
In Dongguan, “more than 90% of the local
motorcycles and electric vehicles have no

103
00:06:07,180 --> 00:06:09,000
license plates.”

104
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:15,130
But when a reporter called the Dongguan city
government hotline to find documents with

105
00:06:15,130 --> 00:06:21,220
rules for confiscating vehicles, the operator
said “It is not clear whether this operation

106
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:24,620
has any relevant documents to reveal.”

107
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:29,940
And the local police said, “Once the latest
legal regulations are confirmed, they will

108
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:32,990
